Interface EngineFactory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface EngineFactory
    An EngineFactory chooses which Engine to instantiate based on the given File.

    • Method Detail

      • newEngine

        EngineBase newEngine(java.io.File file,
                   java.lang.String tableName,
                   TableConfig config)
        Creates a new Engine in the EngineBase.EngineState#Uninitialized state. The engine should be one that is appropriate for the given table.
        Parameters:
        file - A file representing one table in the database, for which an engine is needed.
        tableName - The name of the table for which an engine is needed.
        TableConfig - The TableConfig for the table.
        Returns:
        An appropriate engine for the given file.
